reviews.text: Good Cantonese cuisine focusing on ingredients and proper cooking methods,  not frills or “trendy” tricks. Quality consistent. 銅盆雞、葱油雞、老火湯、芋頭（灣仔店）recommended. A place we visit every now n then. Reservation recommended for Saturday n Friday.

Food at this place is good, especially the sweet and sour pork, fried squid, steam meat cake and soup.  Other dishes are nice too.  The reason why I can't give 5 stars is that only if you are customers that they know you or they know you work for big corporate then the service is very different.  The captain does look down on people which I think the owner of the central shop would need serious consideration.

Environment and location - Good location, it located at Central, just 5 minutes walking distance from Central MTR station. Inside location is cozy too comparatively with all those traditional Chinese restaurant. 

Food - Taste very good and they all cook the dishes in traditional Chinese cooking method. 

Service - Good service, they care about what you need and they help you to change your dishes regularly.
Simply delicious. The steam grouper is one of the best I ever had. Deep-fried calamari is a must order dish.
Very good Cantonese restaurant. The sweet sour deep fried pork is amazing.

result.name: Sing Kee Seafood Restaurant (Central)

reviews.text: Great place for a traditional Cantonese dinner. Reasonable and yummy. Service is great on a weeknight when they are not overwhelmed by the crowd.
Very good restaurant with great food and friendly waiter.
Good food. Not expensive if you don’t order seafood. Average service

I don’t normally leave bad reviews for places, but I went here based on the positive reviews online and from the Michelin guide so I think it’s important to be honest. This was literally the worst Chinese food I have had anywhere on this planet. No one in my group of 4 could eat more than a few bites of their food - it was that bad. It was also insanely overpriced and this was the most we spent on  a meal during our whole trip. The service was good, however.

The food is delicious here but it seems that the branch in Wan Chai is a bit better than this store . I will try again to see whether it’s a busy night or the standard is not as good as the Wan Chai one .

reviews.text:
飯店菜色有水準……不加味精，另每枱加送甜品(陳皮红豆莎)
，值得推介朋友到此之一。
食物一般的水準 算是中上 兩個地鐵站中間 出入都不方便 雖有代客泊車 自己找停車場要行好遠 到萬宜大廈 招呼就真係麻麻地 我做冬嗰日訂咗六點鐘 知道座位緊張 早咗少少到 點知佢話地方淺窄 你落街行下先啦 已經喺地鐵站行到去擺花街再落街行下先 真係一條氣 我話唔介意坐住先佢都話唔得。 今時今日呢啲服務態度 真係唔多得。
